NYC's inverted pop mainstay James K returns, dislodging shoegaze, ambient, power electronics and narcotic techno masonry, rebuilding songs from the rubble. RIYL Eartheater, MBV, Klein, Pharmakon, Mica Levi.

description:
Quirky, noise-damaged instrumental collages that teeter between glitchy YouTube samples, Ableton presets, clattery folk twangs and pristine, glacial classical cinematics. Basically somewhere between Jóhann Jóhannsson, l'ocelle mare and James Ferraro.

              (FAITICHE)
label: FAITICHE
description:
Andrew Pekler's first album as SG is a sentimental, homespun collection of sliced-up guitar compositions that takes Chicago's jazzy post-rock sound and turns its tangled riffs into faint vapors. RIYL Labradford, Tortoise, Fennesz or Oren Ambarchi.
